                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/870: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-30T09:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1928—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>802. Department’s 360, October 26, 5 p.m. Following from consul general at
                    Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Gunboat has not gone alongside, and I am still working with the Chinese
                            authorities as indicated in my October 23, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>2. In view of our treaty rights I considered action of Chinese (other
                            than Maritime Customs) in forcibly seizing bona fide American vessels as
                            an outrage to our flag.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
